A coarse linear opacity in the right upper lung is unchanged dating back to, and likely reflects vascular calcifications.
Impression: Grossly stable bibasilar opacities, likely a combination of atelectasis and bilateral pleural effusions, left greater than right. Improving mild pulmonary edema.
